|switch| - switchIn, always fires
|-status|psn|silent - switchIn if incoming has Toxic status

selectMove: No logs but we determine if skip_turn
    skip_turn if 
        recharging and bound
        rage and bound
        (thrashing or charging) and bound
        // e.g:
        (re/charging, rage, thrashing) and bound
        // but saveMove null is called if rage/thrashing/charging

        (frozen or sleeping or bide) - saveMove w/ choice called

        bound - saveMove choice

    if binding:
        saveMove(choice), return

    otherwise: saveMove if not struggling = move|0

saveMove
    if null just return
    otherwise assert is a move
    if move|0 last_selected_move = Struggle
    else
    last_selected_move = active.move(data)
    battle lastMove(player).index = data

executeMove - no log messages in showdown mode
    beforeMove
    canMove
    if cant
        return
    else 
        doMove

turnOrder - sets nothing, no logs
    uses last_selected_move for priority


beforeMove
    if sleeping:
        |-curestatus| if wake
        |cant| otherwise

    if frozen:
        |cant|
    if bound: |cant|
    if flinch: |cant|
    if recharging: |cant|
    check disable count, |end| if over
    if disabled: |cant|
    "handleConfusion"

handleResidual
    apply status damage
    leech seed

endTurn:
    check if tie, increment turn

doTurn:
    executeMove for each player
    

    


update:
    selectMove for both players - just set last_selected 
        and maybe set skip_turn

    REWRAP if binding and opp switching

    doTurn for both players

    if no more vol.attacks set binding = false

    endTurn